<answer>Since $PQ = PR$, we have $\angle PQR = \angle PRQ = x$. Also, $\angle QRP = 65^\circ$. Therefore, $x + x + 65^\circ = 180^\circ$. So, $$\begin{aligned}

&\phantom{\hphantom{ = 0}}

&\hphantom{2x + }65^\circ

&= 180^\circ - x

&&\text{Subtract }65^\circ\text{ from each side.}\\

&\hphantom{-65^\circ}

&\phantom{2x = 115}

&\hphantom{3x} = 115^\circ

&&\text{Combine like terms.}\\

&\hphantom{-65^\circ}

&\frac{115^\circ}{3}

&= x &&\text{Divide each side by }3\text{.}

\end{aligned}$$

The answer is $\boxed{115^\circ/3}$.
